Nigeriaâ€™s Senate approved plans to
borrow $1.54 billion to finance infrastructure projects,
 BusinessDay  reported, citing the parliamentary debate over the
2011 budget.  The Export/Import Bank of China will lend $900 million for
the Abuja to Kaduna railway, while the World Bank will lend $315
million for public-private partnership projects, the Lagos-based
newspaper reported.  Another $170 million will come from the French Development
Agency for electricity and gas projects, while $152.2 million
will go to the Power Sector Reform Program, BusinessDay
